{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":888,"text":"I, like many of you,"},{"time":2793,"text":"am one of the two billion people\non Earth who live in cities."},{"time":9475,"text":"And there are days --\nI don't know about the rest of you --"},{"time":12414,"text":"but there are days when I palpably feel"},{"time":16000,"text":"how much I rely on other people"},{"time":18501,"text":"for pretty much everything in my life."},{"time":21349,"text":"And some days, that can even\nbe a little scary."},{"time":24694,"text":"But what I'm here\nto talk to you about today"},{"time":26802,"text":"is how that same interdependence"},{"time":29608,"text":"is actually an extremely\npowerful social infrastructure"},{"time":34121,"text":"that we can actually harness"},{"time":36129,"text":"to help heal some\nof our deepest civic issues,"},{"time":40564,"text":"if we apply open-source collaboration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44988,"text":"A couple of years ago,"},{"time":46356,"text":"I read an article by New York Times\nwriter Michael Pollan,"},{"time":49878,"text":"in which he argued that growing\neven some of our own food"},{"time":54001,"text":"is one of the best things\nthat we can do for the environment."},{"time":58036,"text":"Now at the time that I was reading this,"},{"time":59965,"text":"it was the middle of the winter"},{"time":61630,"text":"and I definitely did not have room\nfor a lot of dirt"},{"time":64961,"text":"in my New York City apartment."},{"time":67114,"text":"So I was basically just willing to settle"},{"time":69104,"text":"for just reading the next Wired magazine"},{"time":71074,"text":"and finding out how the experts\nwere going to figure out"},{"time":73718,"text":"how to solve all these problems\nfor us in the future."},{"time":76818,"text":"But that was actually exactly the point"},{"time":79091,"text":"that Michael Pollan\nwas making in this article --"},{"time":81401,"text":"it's precisely when we hand over"},{"time":83634,"text":"the responsibility\nfor all these things to specialists"},{"time":86900,"text":"that we cause the kind of messes\nthat we see with the food system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92000,"text":"So, I happen to know\na little bit from my own work"},{"time":95358,"text":"about how NASA has been using hydroponics"},{"time":99637,"text":"to explore growing food in space."},{"time":102884,"text":"And that you can actually\nget optimal nutritional yield"},{"time":107323,"text":"by running a kind of high-quality\nliquid soil over plants' root systems."},{"time":113931,"text":"Now to a vegetable plant,"},{"time":115540,"text":"my apartment has got to be\nabout as foreign as outer space."},{"time":120050,"text":"But I can offer some natural light"},{"time":122535,"text":"and year-round climate control."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125230,"text":"Fast-forward two years later:"},{"time":126950,"text":"we now have window farms,"},{"time":128698,"text":"which are vertical, hydroponic platforms"},{"time":130775,"text":"for food-growing indoors."},{"time":133624,"text":"And the way it works\nis that there's a pump at the bottom,"},{"time":136403,"text":"which periodically sends this liquid\nnutrient solution up to the top,"},{"time":139980,"text":"which then trickles down\nthrough plants' root systems"},{"time":142648,"text":"that are suspended in clay pellets --"},{"time":144813,"text":"so there's no dirt involved."},{"time":147307,"text":"Now light and temperature vary\nwith each window's microclimate,"},{"time":152038,"text":"so a window farm requires a farmer,"},{"time":155820,"text":"and she must decide"},{"time":157341,"text":"what kind of crops she is going\nto put in her window farm,"},{"time":161100,"text":"and whether she is going\nto feed her food organically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165033,"text":"Back at the time,"},{"time":166208,"text":"a window farm was no more\nthan a technically complex idea"},{"time":169413,"text":"that was going to require\na lot of testing."},{"time":172000,"text":"And I really wanted it\nto be an open project,"},{"time":174774,"text":"because hydroponics"},{"time":176000,"text":"is one of the fastest\ngrowing areas of patenting"},{"time":178740,"text":"in the United States right now,"},{"time":180426,"text":"and could possibly become\nanother area like Monsanto,"},{"time":184121,"text":"where we have a lot of corporate\nintellectual property"},{"time":187185,"text":"in the way of people's food."},{"time":190112,"text":"So I decided that,\ninstead of creating a product,"},{"time":193759,"text":"what I was going to do"},{"time":194950,"text":"was open this up\nto a whole bunch of codevelopers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199359,"text":"The first few systems that we created,\nthey kind of worked."},{"time":202145,"text":"We were actually able to grow\nabout a salad a week"},{"time":204503,"text":"in a typical New York City\napartment window."},{"time":206917,"text":"And we were able to grow cherry tomatoes"},{"time":208970,"text":"and cucumbers, all kinds of stuff."},{"time":210974,"text":"But the first few systems"},{"time":212477,"text":"were these leaky, loud power-guzzlers"},{"time":216032,"text":"that Martha Stewart\nwould definitely never have approved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218814,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":220686,"text":"So to bring on more codevelopers,"},{"time":223095,"text":"what we did was we created\na social media site"},{"time":226021,"text":"on which we published the designs,"},{"time":227990,"text":"we explained how they worked,"},{"time":230008,"text":"and we even went so far"},{"time":232411,"text":"as to point out everything\nthat was wrong with these systems."},{"time":235679,"text":"And then we invited people\nall over the world"},{"time":238071,"text":"to build them and experiment with us."},{"time":241360,"text":"So actually now on this website,"},{"time":243547,"text":"we have 18,000 people."},{"time":246268,"text":"And we have window farms\nall over the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250441,"text":"What we're doing\nis what NASA or a large corporation"},{"time":254237,"text":"would call R&amp;D,\nor research and development."},{"time":257752,"text":"But what we call it is R&amp;D-I-Y,"},{"time":260689,"text":"or \"research and develop it yourself.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":263352,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":264848,"text":"So, for example, Jackson came along"},{"time":267427,"text":"and suggested that we use air pumps\ninstead of water pumps."},{"time":270602,"text":"It took building a whole bunch\nof systems to get it right,"},{"time":273341,"text":"but once we did, we were able to cut\nour carbon footprint nearly in half."},{"time":277874,"text":"Tony in Chicago has been taking on\ngrowing experiments,"},{"time":280882,"text":"like lots of other window farmers,"},{"time":282560,"text":"and he's been able to get\nhis strawberries to fruit"},{"time":285547,"text":"for nine months of the year\nin low-light conditions"},{"time":288330,"text":"by simply changing out\nthe organic nutrients."},{"time":292281,"text":"And window farmers in Finland\nhave been customizing their window farms"},{"time":296679,"text":"for the dark days of the Finnish winters"},{"time":299043,"text":"by outfitting them with LED grow lights"},{"time":301144,"text":"that they're now making\nopen source and part of the project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304461,"text":"So window farms have been evolving"},{"time":306854,"text":"through a rapid versioning process\nsimilar to software."},{"time":310639,"text":"And with every open source project,"},{"time":313333,"text":"the real benefit is the interplay"},{"time":315071,"text":"between the specific concerns\nof people customizing their systems"},{"time":319534,"text":"for their own particular concerns,"},{"time":321377,"text":"and the universal concerns."},{"time":323449,"text":"So my core team and I"},{"time":325406,"text":"are able to concentrate\non the improvements"},{"time":327980,"text":"that really benefit everyone."},{"time":330248,"text":"And we're able to look out\nfor the needs of newcomers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333491,"text":"So for do-it-yourselfers,"},{"time":335245,"text":"we provide free,\nvery well-tested instructions"},{"time":339391,"text":"so that anyone, anywhere around the world,"},{"time":341500,"text":"can build one of these systems for free."},{"time":343673,"text":"And there's a patent pending\non these systems as well"},{"time":346419,"text":"that's held by the community."},{"time":348210,"text":"And to fund the project,"},{"time":350138,"text":"we partner to create products"},{"time":352464,"text":"that we then sell\nto schools and to individuals"},{"time":355365,"text":"who don't have time\nto build their own systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358736,"text":"Now within our community,\na certain culture has appeared."},{"time":362225,"text":"In our culture,\nit is better to be a tester"},{"time":364962,"text":"who supports someone else's idea"},{"time":367255,"text":"than it is to be just the idea guy."},{"time":370449,"text":"What we get out of this project\nis support for our own work,"},{"time":374601,"text":"as well as an experience\nof actually contributing"},{"time":378546,"text":"to the environmental movement"},{"time":380696,"text":"in a way other than just\nscrewing in new light bulbs."},{"time":384155,"text":"But I think that Eleen expresses best"},{"time":386826,"text":"what we really get out of this,"},{"time":388327,"text":"which is the actual joy of collaboration."},{"time":391686,"text":"So she expresses here what it's like"},{"time":394000,"text":"to see someone halfway across the world"},{"time":396501,"text":"having taken your idea, built upon it"},{"time":398827,"text":"and then acknowledging\nyou for contributing."},{"time":401540,"text":"If we really want to see\nthe kind of wide consumer behavior change"},{"time":405471,"text":"that we're all talking about\nas environmentalists and food people,"},{"time":409150,"text":"maybe we just need\nto ditch the term \"consumer\""},{"time":411559,"text":"and get behind the people\nwho are doing stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415379,"text":"Open source projects\ntend to have a momentum of their own."},{"time":418575,"text":"And what we're seeing is that R&amp;D-I-Y"},{"time":420639,"text":"has moved beyond\njust window farms and LEDs"},{"time":424442,"text":"into solar panels and aquaponic systems."},{"time":428633,"text":"And we're building upon innovations\nof generations who went before us."},{"time":432575,"text":"And we're looking ahead at generations"},{"time":434413,"text":"who really need us\nto retool our lives now."},{"time":438415,"text":"So we ask that you join us"},{"time":440204,"text":"in rediscovering the value\nof citizens united,"},{"time":444554,"text":"and to declare\nthat we are all still pioneers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449270,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}